  "tips": [
    "The town of Benasque is located at the foot of the Posets and Maladeta massifs, in an immense valley and where the town reaches more than a thousand meters in height. The Bensaque valley is one of the best-known pubs in this part of the Pyrenees.",
    "The Linsoles (or Eriste) Reservoir was built in the 1960s to collect the water channeled through the mountain to power the Eriste hydroelectric power station. It is one of the 3 reservoirs of the Ésera river in the Benasque valley.",
    "Anciles is a small town that is all paved, its streets and houses, even the church ... Your visit is highly recommended."
